Note:
UML conventions are followed throughtout and I will list some of them here if you are unaware of them.
1.For fields:
+ public
- private
# protected
~ default(no access specifier)
/ derived
static fields are explicitly mentioned
2.For methods:
methodName():return_type
void return types are omitted. The symbols before the method name are the same as the fields.
3. Abstract class' names are in italics
4. Interfaces are mentioned explicitly above the name in double angular brackets :<<interface>>
5.Dark arrow pointing shows inheritance so A->B implies A is derived from B
5.1 White solid arrow means B is abstract
5.2 White dotted arrow is used when A implements B and B is an interface
6.Fields in CAPS implies it is a final field
